{
  "stem": "13469.4",
  "chunk_idx": 8,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And many Jewish people in Holland had been able to get these Palestine certificates.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Obviously, people in Holland realized the benefits of these exchanges.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Everybody must have known about this exchange business so everybody desperately tried to get these Palestine certificates.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And, again, we have notes here that we applied for Palestine certificates from our aunt who was living in Palestine at that time, Liesel.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We applied for certificates for our paternal grandparents, which were her parents, but we never got them in time.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And we also applied for Palestine certificates for us, for our family, in case the British thing didn't work.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "But we don't think we ever got those, in the end.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "There was a lot of correspondence that they'd been applied for and all this sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "But we gather the only time they worked is if you actually had the number on the certificate.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And all this went by the Red Cross and by the Swiss embassy and by this, that, and everything else.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "It took ages to get these things sorted out.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And, in our case, we don't think we ever actually got the Palestine certificates.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "But a lot of other people did, and, as I say, these people, [INAUDIBLE] that lived across the road from us in [INAUDIBLE], they had the Palestine certificates, and they were actually exchanged.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "So it did work.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "The other people who had the blue stamps were people who had entry visas for various South American countries like Nicaragua and Colombia and Venezuela and all that sort of thing.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "We understand that you could buy those visas in Holland before you went [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "You couldn't buy them in Westerbork anymore.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "But in Amsterdam and previously, you could buy those certificates for loads of money.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
